#!N  #!Rdirect Direction #!N #!N Category #!N #!N  #!Lcattrn,dxall763 h Transformation  #!EL  
#!N #!N Function #!N #!N Converts azimuth, elevation, and distance to 
an [x, y, z] position. #!N #!N Syntax #!CForestGreen #!N #!N 
 #!F-adobe-courier-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N point #!EF = Direction(  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   azimuth, elevation, distance 
#!EF ); #!EF #!N #!N #!EC #!N #!N Inputs #!T,1,91,276,461,646  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--14*   
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N TAB Name TAB Type TAB Default TAB Description #!EF 
#!N TAB azimuth TAB scalar TAB 0 TAB azimuth in degrees 
#!N TAB elevation TAB scalar TAB 0 TAB elevation in degrees 
#!N TAB distance TAB scalar TAB 1 TAB distance #!N TAB 
- TAB - TAB - TAB #!EF #!N #!N Outputs #!T,1,161,321,646 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--14*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   #!N TAB Name TAB Type TAB Description #!EF #!N 
TAB point TAB vector TAB x, y, z position #!N TAB 
- TAB - TAB #!EF #!N #!N Functional Details #!N #!N 
The output of Direction can be used, for example, as input 
to the Camera or AutoCamera module to set the look-from direction. 
#!N #!I0 #!N #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   azimuth #!EF #!EF 
#!I50 #!N the angular distance (in degrees) from the positive  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   
z #!EF -axis to the positive  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   x #!EF -axis. #!N 
#!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   elevation #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N the angular 
distance (in degrees) from the positive  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   xz #!EF plane toward 
the positive  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   y #!EF -axis. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*    #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
distance #!EF #!EF #!I50 #!N is measured in user units. #!I0 
